INSERT OR IGNORE INTO hotels (name, slug, description, city, country, address, latitude, longitude, amenities, property_type, cancellation_policy, created_at, is_active) VALUES ('Iconic Bali Landmarks: GWK Statue &amp; Uluwatu Temple Sunset Experience', 'iconic-bali-landmarks-gwk-statue-uluwatu-temple-sunset-experience-copy', 'Witness the grand scale of Balinese ambition and the raw beauty of the Indian Ocean in one high-impact afternoon. This curated express tour is designed for travelers who want to experience Bali’s most iconic southern landmarks without the slow pace of a standard group excursion. We focus on "The Big Two"—the colossal architecture of the Garuda Wisnu Kencana (GWK) and the spiritual clifftop serenity of Uluwatu Temple.

Your journey begins at GWK Cultural Park, a masterpiece of modern engineering and ancient mythology. Standing at 121 meters, the statue of Lord Vishnu riding the mythical bird Garuda is one of the tallest in the world, offering a scale of grandeur that defines the Bukit Peninsula skyline. Your private guide will streamline your visit through the massive limestone plazas and cultural galleries, ensuring you capture the best angles of the statue without the guesswork.

As the afternoon light begins to soften, we head to the southwestern tip of the island to Uluwatu Temple. Perched 70 meters above a sheer cliff face, this ancient sea temple is a testament to Bali’s spiritual heritage. We time our arrival to beat the peak sunset rush, allowing you to walk the scenic cliff-top paths and soak in the panoramic ocean views before the major crowds arrive. This is Bali at its most dramatic—delivered with the efficiency and comfort of a private, expert-led experience.

✨ Tour Highlights
The Colossal 121m Titan: Marvel at the Garuda Wisnu Kencana statue, a monumental symbol of protection and one of the world’s most impressive cultural landmarks.

Cliff-Edge Spirituality: Explore the 11th-century Uluwatu Temple, uniquely situated on a steep cliff overlooking the world-class surf breaks of the Indian Ocean.

Fast-Track Logistics: An optimized route designed to bypass the heaviest traffic bottlenecks, maximizing your time at the actual sites.

Private Expert Insights: Gain a deeper understanding of Balinese mythology, Hindu philosophy, and the 28-year history behind the GWK statue.

Breathtaking Ocean Panoramas: Walk the historic clifftop boundary of Uluwatu for the most iconic sunset and photography spots on the island.

Seamless Door-to-Door Service: Travel in the comfort of a private, air-conditioned vehicle with flexible hotel pickup and drop-off, perfect for travelers on a tight schedule.

-ITINERARY -

13:30 (01:30 PM): Hotel Pickup (Nusa Dua, Jimbaran, Kuta, or Seminyak).

14:00 (02:00 PM): Arrive at GWK Cultural Park.

Explore the 121m Vishnu Statue, Lotus Pond, and plazas.

15:45 (03:45 PM): Depart for Uluwatu.

16:15 (04:15 PM): Arrive at Uluwatu Temple.

Explore the clifftop temple and take panoramic photos.

17:15 (05:15 PM): Enter the Amphitheater.

PM Note: It is vital to enter early to secure the best seats for the sunset backdrop.

18:00 (06:00 PM): Kecak &amp; Fire Dance Performance.

Experience the rhythmic chanting and fire show as the sun sets.

19:00 (07:00 PM): Performance ends. Meet your driver at the designated point.

20:15 (08:15 PM): Return arrival at your hotel.

Note: Return time is later due to high traffic volume exiting Uluwatu after the show.


- INCLUSIONS -

Hotel ick up and drop off, Private AC vehicle, fuel, and parking fees.

English-speaking driver/guide.
(Note: Entrance tickets to GWK, Uluwatu Temple, and the Kecak Show are not included unless pre-arranged).


- IMPORTANT INFO -

Kecak Tickets: These often sell out. We recommend booking tickets in advance or arriving at the theater by 5:15 PM.

Dress Code: Shoulders and knees must be covered (sarongs are usually provided at the temple entrance).

Monkey Warning: Please keep all jewelry, sunglasses, and loose items secure inside the temple grounds.', 'Bali', 'indonesia', 'Jalan Majapahit No.45, Kuta, Kabupaten Badung, Bali, Indonesia., Denpasar, Indonesia, 80361', -8.7169125, 115.1790205, '[]', 'Hotel', 'The following cancellation policy is set forth on our website and applies at the time of reservation.\nCancellation on the day of use will incur a cancellation fee of 100% of the usage fee.\nCancellation up to 24 hours prior to the start of use will not incur a cancellation fee.', '2026-02-25 13:09:32', 1);
